Jordan Stephen Roberts (born 5 January 1994) is an English professional footballer who plays as a striker for Scottish Premiership club Motherwell.
Roberts has previously played for Tamworth, Havant & Waterlooville, Bishop's Stortford, Aldershot Town, Inverness Caledonian Thistle, Crawley Town, Lincoln City, Gillingham, Heart of Midlothian and Ipswich Town.

On 20 September 2013, Young joined Football Conference side Aldershot Town on a six-month contract. A day later, Young made his Aldershot debut in their 2–0 victory over Wrexham, featuring for 67 minutes before being replaced by Jordan Roberts.
